TL:DR - no more hanging around or studying in the warren
Hey Fennerites,
Following a meeting today, use of the warren as a common space has been restricted. You will not be able to loiter or spend time there anymore. this includes using the couches and game equipment, which you will notice have been removed. Additionally, the bar will no longer be running. Sarah has made some easy to follow guidelines which I have attached below. Stay safe and follow the rules everyone, they're there for our protection.

Hi everyone, I am leaving tomorrow morning. Now, I know grand announcements of departure aren't fashionable around here. But I wanted to announce I am leaving because I have a few items that are almost new that I am unable to take with me, and I'd like them to go to a good home.
I have some bags of frozen mashed potatos, frozen onions, 2 good pots, a brand new block of lurpak butter and an unopened bag of parmesan cheese, vinegar (chinese)
Please let me know if you would like any of the items.

DUTY WARDEN - VERY IMPORTANT - KITCHEN BAY LIMITS: LARGE BAYS - 2 PEOPLE, CORNER BAY - 1 PERSON
Kitchen bay limits have been updated: for the main bays (large, long ones), it is now 2 PEOPLE max. For the small corner bay, it is 1 PERSON max. Once again, I know this is frustrating, but it is a measure that has been put in place by the university to protect all of our residents. Please be mindful of these changes and adhere to the guidelines immediately. Fenner looks after Fenner.

DUTY WARDEN - VERY IMPORTANT - WARREN AREA CLOSED:
The Warren area is CLOSED. This means that you cannot be in the downstairs area on level 1 (not just the bar/cafe, this includes the games/social area as well). I know this is frustrating, but please keep in mind that this is to keep you all safe! You may enter through the Warren door but you must not hang around in the space. It is extremely important that we all obey these rules and look after each other in these tough times â¤ï¸

This will likely occur at the same time as the general first year rep elections (usually around week 3) but will be open to all students, first year or not. The position of first year sports rep will be available at the same time. I encourage you all to have a think before you return as to whether you would be interested in the position. For those that have filled out a returner application for next year and are wondering whether or not you have to do/redo the Consent Matters module...
If you have never completed Consent Matters, you need to do this by tonight or ASAP.
If you know you have completed Consent Matters in the past, ANU states "If you have previously completed, you are still required to do the module as a refresher course". However this was not adequately communicated to us so do not stress if you cannot redo it by tonight, it will not affect your application. If you have the time in the near future it would be a good idea to redo it but the main thing is that you have completed it at some point in the past.

According to most studies, peopleâ€™s number one fear is public speaking. Number two is death. Death is number two? Does that sound right? This means to the average person, if you go to a funeral, youâ€™re better off in the casket than delivering the eulogy.
Well my friends: I know you all too well to call you ladies and gentlemen - my job as Fenner Public Speaking coach this year is to breakdown this misconception of one of the most powerful forms of communication and ensure that our Public Speaking team will leave Fenner Hall proud!

Fenner Hall IB is looking for a Cheerleader!!! If you think you have what it takes to both cheer and lead then apply below. Sign ups close on Friday at 6pm
The Fenner Hall IB 2019 Cheerleader will be in charge of all things advertising, ranging from creation of a magazine to leading our hall in cheering on our runners as they come into endpoint.
This role is a long term as applications will close on 26th July and IB is on the 4th-5th of October. It will require work throughout the duration picking up in intensity as the event draws closer. (more detailed description in the form below)
